#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.137"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.137:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.137:0.2"
msgid "14. Yodhājīvavagga"
msgstr "14. A Warrior"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.137:0.3"
msgid "137. Kesakambalasutta"
msgstr "137. A Hair Blanket"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.137:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yāni kānici tantāvutānaṃ vatthānaṃ, kesakambalo "
"tesaṃ paṭikiṭṭho akkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a hair blanket is said to be the worst kind of woven cloth."

msgctxt "an3.137:1.2"
msgid ""
"Kesakambalo, bhikkhave, sīte sīto, uṇhe uṇho, dubbaṇṇo, duggandho, "
"dukkhasamphasso."
msgstr ""
"It’s cold in the cold, hot in the heat, ugly, smelly, and unpleasant to "
"touch."

# Note that BB has “various” here for puth, whereas he normally has “ordinary”. I think “various” is preferred always.
#. VAR: puthusamaṇabrāhmaṇavādānaṃ → puthusamaṇappavādānaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.137:1.3"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yāni kānici puthusamaṇabrāhmaṇavādānaṃ makkhalivādo "
"tesaṃ paṭikiṭṭho akkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, the teaching of Makkhali is said to be the worst of all the "
"doctrines of the various ascetics and brahmins."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli1.287"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.137:2.1"
msgid "Makkhali, bhikkhave, moghapuriso evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi:"
msgstr "Makkhali, that foolish man, has this doctrine and view:"

msgctxt "an3.137:2.2"
msgid "‘natthi kammaṃ, natthi kiriyaṃ, natthi vīriyan’ti."
msgstr "‘There is no power in deeds, action, or energy.’"

msgctxt "an3.137:2.3"
msgid ""
"Yepi te, bhikkhave, ahesuṃ atītamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, tepi "
"bhagavanto kammavādā ceva ahesuṃ kiriyavādā ca vīriyavādā ca."
msgstr ""
"Now, all the perfected ones, the fully awakened Buddhas who lived in the "
"past taught the efficacy of deeds, action, and energy."

msgctxt "an3.137:2.4"
msgid "Tepi, bhikkhave, makkhali moghapuriso paṭibāhati:"
msgstr "But Makkhali opposes them by saying:"

msgctxt "an3.137:2.5"
msgid "‘natthi kammaṃ, natthi kiriyaṃ, natthi vīriyan’ti."
msgstr "‘There is no power in deeds, action, or energy.’"

msgctxt "an3.137:2.6"
msgid ""
"Yepi te, bhikkhave, bhavissanti anāgatamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, "
"tepi bhagavanto kammavādā ceva bhavissanti kiriyavādā ca vīriyavādā ca."
msgstr ""
"All the perfected ones, the fully awakened Buddhas who will live in the "
"future will teach the efficacy of deeds, action, and energy."

msgctxt "an3.137:2.7"
msgid "Tepi, bhikkhave, makkhali moghapuriso paṭibāhati:"
msgstr "But Makkhali opposes them by saying:"

msgctxt "an3.137:2.8"
msgid "‘natthi kammaṃ, natthi kiriyaṃ, natthi vīriyan’ti."
msgstr "‘There is no power in deeds, action, or energy.’"

msgctxt "an3.137:2.9"
msgid ""
"Ahampi, bhikkhave, etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho kammavādo ceva kiriyavādo "
"ca vīriyavādo ca."
msgstr ""
"I too, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha in the present, teach "
"the efficacy of deeds, action, and energy."

msgctxt "an3.137:2.10"
msgid "Mampi, bhikkhave, makkhali moghapuriso paṭibāhati:"
msgstr "But Makkhali opposes me by saying:"

msgctxt "an3.137:2.11"
msgid "‘natthi kammaṃ, natthi kiriyaṃ, natthi vīriyan’ti."
msgstr "‘There is no power in deeds, action, or energy.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: khippaṃ → khipaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: uḍḍeyya → oḍḍeyya (bj)
#. VAR: bahūnaṃ → bahunnaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.137:3.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, nadīmukhe khippaṃ uḍḍeyya bahūnaṃ macchānaṃ ahitāya "
"dukkhāya anayāya byasanāya;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like a trap set at the mouth of a river, which would bring harm, "
"suffering, calamity, and disaster for many fish."

msgctxt "an3.137:3.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, makkhali moghapuriso manussakhippaṃ maññe loke "
"uppanno bahūnaṃ sattānaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya anayāya byasanāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way that foolish man Makkhali is a trap for humans, it seems to "
"me. He has come into the world for the harm, suffering, calamity, and "
"disaster of many beings.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.137:3.3"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
